01:58:02,642 --> 01:58:05,945
and the First Amendment states,
"Congress shall make no law

2159
01:58:05,978 --> 01:58:07,947
impeding the freedom
of the press."

2160
01:58:07,980 --> 01:58:11,551
That meant, to me,
that no matter which representative told me

2161
01:58:11,584 --> 01:58:16,622
that I couldn't come in that day, the
Constitution guaranteed my rights.

2162
01:58:19,225 --> 01:58:21,227
FOX: Has press
already gone in?

2163
01:58:21,260 --> 01:58:22,662
There's no press covering.

2164
01:58:22,695 --> 01:58:26,199
No credentialed media
signed up to cover the hearing. Uh-huh.

2165
01:58:26,232 --> 01:58:29,569
FOX, VOICE-OVER: Of course, I knew what
might happen. I didn't think it would.

2166
01:58:29,602 --> 01:58:31,604
I thought they would
actually cave and realize

2167
01:58:31,637 --> 01:58:33,739
that we were on the right side
of the First Amendment.

2168
01:58:33,773 --> 01:58:36,742
But I have to say
I wasn't surprised.

2169
01:58:36,776 --> 01:58:39,712
WOMAN: Sir, you are not
allowed in with a camera.

2170
01:58:39,745 --> 01:58:43,216
FOX, VOICE-OVER: It had been
demonstrated to me over and over again

2171
01:58:43,249 --> 01:58:46,385
that certain elements
within Congress and the gas industry

2172
01:58:46,419 --> 01:58:50,456
had gotten used to treating the Constitution
just as they had treated the fossil fuels

2173
01:58:50,490 --> 01:58:56,129
they extracted, as a relic left behind from
the past that they had every right to burn.

2174
01:58:56,162 --> 01:58:58,097
WOMAN: You cannot
have that in here.

2175
01:58:58,131 --> 01:59:00,199
FOX: Of course we can.
It's a public meeting. No, you cannot.

2176
01:59:00,233 --> 01:59:02,201
There's an appeal to the Chair.

2177
01:59:02,235 --> 01:59:04,670
Several of the members are
going to make a statement.

2178
01:59:04,704 --> 01:59:07,039
Sir. And we are allowed to
be here, within our rights.

2179
01:59:07,073 --> 01:59:09,041
Are you going
to remove your camera?

2180
01:59:09,075 --> 01:59:12,311
I... I am not going
to remove the camera.

2181
01:59:13,713 --> 01:59:16,816
Sir, sir, stop.

2182
01:59:18,184 --> 01:59:21,154
FOX: We have
also sent emails.

2183
01:59:21,187 --> 01:59:24,957
We have also sent emails
and we have talked. Yes.

2184
01:59:24,991 --> 01:59:26,626
Do your duty,
Officer. All right.

2185
01:59:26,659 --> 01:59:29,662
Sir, turn around, put your hands
behind your back for me, please.

2186
01:59:31,030 --> 01:59:34,667
MAN: Come on, come on.
Come on, Mr. Chairman.

2187
01:59:36,035 --> 01:59:38,504
Mr. Chair, we discussed
this before.

2188
01:59:38,538 --> 01:59:41,507
Ahem. This is
a public hearing.

2189
01:59:41,541 --> 01:59:44,076
This is a public hearing.

2190
01:59:44,110 --> 01:59:46,012
I'm within my First
Amendment rights,

2191
01:59:46,045 --> 01:59:48,681
and I am being taken out.

2192
01:59:50,149 --> 01:59:52,485
MAN: Well, but before
the meeting has begun,

2193
01:59:52,518 --> 01:59:56,856
before we've had a chance to discuss the issues,
