2194
02:00:00,193 --> 02:00:01,727
WOMAN: Where's the transparency?

2195
02:00:05,364 --> 02:00:07,867
FOX, VOICE-OVER: They led me out
of the hearing room.

2196
02:00:07,900 --> 02:00:09,869
I was told I was the first
journalist to be arrested

2197
02:00:09,902 --> 02:00:12,305
in Congress simply
for doing journalism,

2198
02:00:12,338 --> 02:00:14,373
but we really wanted
to tape the hearing.

2199
02:00:14,407 --> 02:00:16,776
We really wanted to hear
what they had to say.

2200
02:00:16,809 --> 02:00:21,080
The great irony is that
after taping 3 1/2 years of hearings

2201
02:00:21,113 --> 02:00:24,050
all across the nation,
in big places and small,

2202
02:00:24,083 --> 02:00:27,587
the last thing I ever want
to do ever again

2203
02:00:27,620 --> 02:00:29,722
is tape a goddamn hearing.

2204
02:00:29,755 --> 02:00:31,691
You got to stand on your feet
the whole time,

2205
02:00:31,724 --> 02:00:33,759
most of what's said is
pretty boring.

2206
02:00:33,793 --> 02:00:35,695
It's a pretty arduous deal.

2207
02:00:35,728 --> 02:00:38,197
When they led me out
in handcuffs, I was half-relieved

2208
02:00:38,231 --> 02:00:41,200
that I didn't have to keep
standing there listening to these people.

2209
02:00:41,234 --> 02:00:44,237
I felt calm. I felt relaxed.
I felt free.

2210
02:00:44,270 --> 02:00:47,440
I didn't have to answer
my phone, return a text message,

2211
02:00:47,473 --> 02:00:49,909
make sure that the camera wasn't
running out of batteries.

2212
02:00:49,942 --> 02:00:52,245
I didn't have to listen to what
these people were saying,

2213
02:00:52,278 --> 02:00:54,447
attacking my friends
in Pavillion, Wyoming,

2214
02:00:54,480 --> 02:00:56,582
attacking the EPA once more.

2215
02:00:56,616 --> 02:01:00,186
I had done everything I needed
to do at that moment.

2216
02:01:00,219 --> 02:01:01,687
There wasn't any more.

2217
02:01:01,721 --> 02:01:04,156
After 3 1/2 years of recording,

2218
02:01:04,190 --> 02:01:07,660
documenting, writing notes,
traveling all over the world,

2219
02:01:07,693 --> 02:01:10,830
this was the most
that I could do.

2220
02:01:27,046 --> 02:01:28,881
When I was in
the police station,

2221
02:01:28,914 --> 02:01:32,385
my arresting officer hit me up
for a part in my next movie

2222
02:01:32,418 --> 02:01:34,820
as he was leading me over
to the fingerprint machine.

2223
02:01:34,854 --> 02:01:36,822
When they pressed my fingers
down on the glass,

2224
02:01:36,856 --> 02:01:39,025
and I saw the images
up on the screen...

2225
02:01:39,058 --> 02:01:41,294
the ridges, the circles

2226
02:01:41,327 --> 02:01:43,896
on my fingertips...
I realized

2227
02:01:43,929 --> 02:01:45,865
they looked just like
the inside of a tree.

2228
02:01:45,898 --> 02:01:50,770
Maybe there's something deep in our DNA
that doesn't want to get cut down.

2229
02:01:50,803 --> 02:01:54,273
Maybe there's something linked.
At least that's what I feel.

2230
02:01:54,307 --> 02:01:56,809
A tree doesn't move
until you cut it down,

2231
02:01:56,842 --> 02:01:59,812
and I'm certainly... not moving.

2232
02:01:59,845 --> 02:02:01,847
We can't all just move,

2233
02:02:01,881 --> 02:02:04,950
certainly not when there's
another way out.

2234
02:02:04,984 --> 02:02:07,820
I felt like I could see it...
a horizontal well bore

2235
02:02:07,853 --> 02:02:12,191
drilled down into the earth,
snaking underneath the Congress,

2236
02:02:12,224 --> 02:02:15,728
shooting money up
through the chamber at such high pressure

2237
02:02:15,761 --> 02:02:18,230
that it blew the top off
of our democracy,

2238
02:02:18,264 --> 02:02:21,434
another layer of contamination
due to fracking;

2239
02:02:21,467 --> 02:02:23,903
not the water, not the air,

2240
02:02:23,936 --> 02:02:26,605
but our government... all
those toxic dollars,

2241
02:02:26,639 --> 02:02:29,642
all those contaminants,
all of that influence

2242
02:02:29,675 --> 02:02:32,144
out-sizing the citizen's voice

2243
02:02:32,178 --> 02:02:34,113
in our democratic republic.

2244
02:02:34,146 --> 02:02:36,682
So I still don't know what's
going to happen around here.

2245
02:02:36,716 --> 02:02:42,221
The saying goes, "Environmentalists
only ever get temporary victories."

2246
02:02:42,254 --> 02:02:45,691
But the losses are
always permanent.

2247
02:02:45,725 --> 02:02:48,728
There's no such thing
as anyone's backyard anymore.

2248
02:02:48,761 --> 02:02:50,696
This wasn't about me
getting drilled

2249
02:02:50,730 --> 02:02:53,799
or anyone getting drilled
in any one place.

2250
02:02:53,833 --> 02:02:56,769
The plan is for shale gas

2251
02:02:56,802 --> 02:02:59,772
to be the new world energy.

2252
02:02:59,805 --> 02:03:01,841
If they get their way,

2253
02:03:01,874 --> 02:03:05,511
we're in for 50 years
of shale gas running the world.

2254
02:03:06,912 --> 02:03:08,848
You start to get dizzy.

2255
02:03:08,881 --> 02:03:11,016
I felt like I could
close my eyes

2256
